LN-1 HELD-OUT GATE (b3_train_wc_holdout on the N=61 natural-fact selector dataset, 2026-07-01)
data: _faithful_corpus/ln1_data.npz (61 queries / 61 episodes, clean global-K via k_<id>.bin)
default (r=32, no reg):   train-diagonal 43/49=87.8%  | HOLDOUT top-1 2/12=16.7%  (6 misses -> trained needle)
regularized (dropout0.4 wd2e-3): train 45/49=91.8%   | HOLDOUT top-1 1/12=8.3%   (11/12 -> trained needle; WORSE)
VERDICT: the latent W_c selector does NOT generalize to unseen natural facts at N=61. Regularization worsens it.
Jaccard oracle = 100% by construction (token-overlap matches the actual tokens) and stays the deployed selector.
W_c generalizes for high-entropy NOVEL needles (360/361, its trained domain); natural facts are mutually too similar
in global-K/Q for a 16K-param r=32 projection at this scale. Latent graduation of THIS sub-task is unproven; either
a much larger corpus (cf. the original 200-needle W_c) or it is a symbolic-op-wins case. Honest negative; methodology held.
